DEV TECH SHEET (TALIC)

1) BUILD DEFINITION
- Feature: API bot architecture and implementation guide.
- Audience: developers implementing resilient autonomous bots.
- Problem solved: removes ambiguity and enforces safe, deterministic behavior.
- Runtime: event-driven or scheduled loop with bounded retries and safe degradation.

2) USER EXPERIENCE DESIGN (OPERATORS/DEVS)
- Happy flow: bot processes events, validates inputs/responses, mutates state only in MODE_NORMAL.
- Alternative flow: transient errors trigger retries; exhaustion degrades to MODE_READ_ONLY; unrecoverable issues enter MODE_IDLE_SAFE.
- UI impact: none (no end-user UI in scope).

3) TECHNICAL NEEDS
- Data model requirements:
  - mode_state (enum: NORMAL, RETRYING, READ_ONLY, IDLE_SAFE)
  - idempotency_key per mutating operation
  - operation ledger for replay safety
- Core components:
  - input validator
  - external response validator
  - idempotent command handler
  - retry policy adapter (tenacity)
  - degradation mode controller
  - structured logger + metrics emitter
- Dependency notes:
  - tenacity for retry/backoff
  - structured logging stack
  - metrics backend integration

4) TESTING & SECURITY
- Unit tests:
  - mode transition rules
  - idempotency invariants
  - retry classification (transient vs permanent)
- Regression tests:
  - restart + replay produces identical state
  - failed mutations do not alter state
- Security checks:
  - no dynamic eval/reflection
  - assertion paths active in production builds

5) WORK PLAN (MVP)
- Milestone 1: contracts + enums + invariants.
- Milestone 2: retry/degradation engine.
- Milestone 3: idempotent mutation pipeline.
- Milestone 4: observability and operational metrics.
- Risks:
  - external API schema drift
  - retry storms under sustained outages

6) RIPPLE EFFECTS
- Update implementation docs for mode semantics.
- Update runbooks for recovery conditions.
- Communicate operational guarantees to stakeholders.

7) BROADER CONTEXT
- Current limitation: single-bot/single-domain scope.
- Future extension: multi-domain orchestration with strict isolation boundaries.
- Moonshot: formally verify critical invariants for state transitions.
